Configure data selection for Linux
Ignore this element.

1. 	
Start a terminal.
2. 	
As superuser, navigate to the Edge System installation directory: /opt/EdgeSystem.
3. 	
To configure data selection, do one of the following
•	
Type in the properties and their values through a command as shown in this example:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host Configuration ConnectivityComponentID DataSelection Selected=true Name=Random NodeId=3

•	
import a .json file through a command as shown in this example:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host Configuration ConnectivityComponentID DataSelection import SampleFilePath/SampleConfigurations.json

4. 	
Optional: To view configured data selection, run this command:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host Configuration ConnectivityComponentID DataSelection

5. 	
Optional: To remove a configured data selection
a. 	
Copy the NodeId of the data selection that you want to remove.
b. 	
Run this command:

./OSIsoft.Data.System.Host Configuration ConnectivityComponentID DataSelection delete NodeId=NodeId
